related_questions.snippet: Is Cheddar Cheese Healthy? Cheddar cheese is a good source of protein, calcium, and phosphorus, making it a nutritious addition to a balanced diet. However, it's also high in saturated fat and sodium, so it's important to enjoy it in moderation.

related_questions.question: Why is cheddar called cheddar?
related_questions.snippet: Why is it called cheddar? Cheeses were traditionally named after their place of origin and thus cheddar is the namesake of its birthplace: Cheddar, England.

buttons.subtitle: Ingredients In Cheddar Cheese
buttons.title: How to Make Cheddar Cheese
buttons.snippet: Cheddar cheese is made with the same ingredients as most other cheeses – milk, salt, rennet, and a bacteria culture. The bacteria is added to cow's milk to acidify it and the rennet is added to curdle it. The curds are strained to separate the liquid whey, then heated to release more whey as the curd melts together.
